<p class="p">During the 
 <italic class="italic">multi-level regression</italic> step, we estimate the relationship of individual and geography-level covariates to a specific climate and energy opinion, h, for a given individual, i, represented by 
 <italic class="italic">y</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">h</italic>[
  <italic class="italic">i</italic>]
 </sub>. For example, we could estimate the relationship between belief that climate change is occuring (h), and a number of individidual demographic characteristics (i). For clarity, we specify the model here for a single opinion only, dropping the indexing over h. At the individual-level, we thus have: 
 <disp-formula id="pone.0159774.e001" class="disp-formula">
